# Project Management Tracker API

Flask-based backend that provides authentication, authorization, and persistence for the Project Management Tracker web application. The service is designed with GDPR and NDPR compliance in mind and aligns with the architecture documented in `../docs/backend-architecture.md`.

## Features (Phase 1)

- JWT authentication with rotating refresh tokens and Argon2id password hashing
- Role-based access control (owner/admin/member/viewer)
- CRUD endpoints for users, teams, boards, lists, and cards
- AI endpoints for board summaries and prompt-driven task suggestions
- Audit logging, consent tracking, and DSR workflows
- Rate limiting, structured logging, and health checks

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.12+
- PostgreSQL 15+
- Redis 7+ (for rate limiting + token revocation)
- (Optional) Docker & Docker Compose for containerized development

### Setup

```bash
cd server
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -e .[dev]
cp .env.example .env
flask db upgrade
flask run --debug
```

The service will start at `http://127.0.0.1:5000` by default.

### Testing

```bash
python -m pytest -q tests
```

### Environment Variables (`.env`)

| Variable | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `FLASK_ENV` | `development` / `production` |
| `SECRET_KEY` | Flask secret key for sessions + JWT signing fallback |
| `JWT_SECRET_KEY` | Signing key for access tokens (rotate regularly) |
| `DATABASE_URL` | SQLAlchemy URL (e.g., `postgresql+psycopg://user:pass@localhost:5432/pmt`) |
| `REDIS_URL` | Redis connection string |
| `ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRES` | Access token lifetime in minutes (default 15) |
| `REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRES` | Refresh token lifetime in days (default 7) |
| `RATE_LIMIT` | Default rate limit string (e.g., `100/minute`) |
| `CORS_ORIGINS` | Comma-separated list of allowed origins |
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | (Optional) API key used for AI summaries and prompts. When unset, deterministic fallbacks are used. |
| `OPENAI_MODEL` | Override the default OpenAI model (`gpt-4o-mini`). |
| `AI_PROVIDER` | Display name for the AI provider (default `openai`). |

